quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  4,20,"But if you wish to exchange one wife for another, and have given one of them a dower (money, gold), then take nothing back from it. What! Would you take it by slander and manifest wrong"
  4,21,"How can you take it when one of you has gone in unto the other, and they have taken from you a solemn contract"
  4,22,"And do not marry women your fathers married - except what has already happened - for it is an abominable and hateful practice, and an evil way"
  4,23,"Unlawful for you are your mothers, and your daughters, and your sisters, and your paternal aunts and maternal aunts, and your brother´s daughters, and your sister´s daughters, and your foster mothers, and your foster sisters, and your wive&acu"